extends layout

block title
  h1.hidden-xs Trumplines

block canvas
  script(type='text/javascript' src='js/sketch.js')
  .popup
    h1#intro.hidden-xs
      |Trumplines
    img(src='img/trump.png' width='100%' class="visible-xs")
    .container
        .row
          .mobile.visible-xs
            .attribution
              |Original photo credit: 
              a(href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0")
                |Gage Skidmore
            br
            |Trumplines just isn't the same on a mobile screen. Please view this on a computer or tablet.
          .intro.col-sm-9.col-md-7.col-lg-6.hidden-xs
            br
            button(type="button" class="btn btn-lg" title="Start!" alt="Start!")
              |START TRUMPLINES
            p
            br
            |Explore Donald Trump's public image, as pieced together here using headlines published by the New York Times, from 1976 up to his declaration of candidacy on June 16th, 2015.
            p
            |Just make a selection in the timeline, and you will be able to explore that year's Trump-related headlines. Feel free to click a headline to view the original article on the New York Times website.
            br
            br
            br
            p
              b
                |FOREWORD
            |Like many public figures, Trump has had his ups and downs in the public eye &mdash; but what you will see as you browse the headlines is a very interesting person and persona: becoming increasingly outspoken year-by-year.
            p
            |If you have any sort of an itch to understand why Trump may very well win the 2016 US presidential election, this is recommended reading.
            p
            |To help, all headlines have been run through a sentiment analysis program. Green and red highlighting indicates that a headline carries positive or negative sentiment, respectively. Neutral headlines are simply black.
            br
            br
            p
              b
                |Edward Cheng 2016
              br
              .attribution
                |Original background photo credit: 
                a(href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/")
                  |Jamelle Bouie

